---

## What "done" looks like

A successful project produces three artifacts at the project root:

| Artifact | Source | What it is |
|---|---|---|
| `model.orm.yaml` | Phases 1–3 | The conceptual ORM 2 model: object types, fact types, constraints, source provenance |
| `model.verbalization.txt` | Phase 4 | Halpin-style Controlled Natural Language verbalization of every fact type and constraint |
| `model.py` | Phase 5 | PyRel translation of the YAML, ready to load into RAI |

The `model.orm.yaml` is the source of truth. Verbalization and PyRel are derived from it.

---

## The skill behind this project

This project uses the `rai-orm-from-text` skill, which implements Halpin's CSDP (Conceptual Schema Design Procedure). The skill is loaded automatically when Claude Code starts in this directory.

CSDP is **dialogue-driven**. Each phase's `/gsd:discuss-phase` step is where you (acting as modeler) and the domain expert verbalize examples, confirm uniqueness, and label subtypes. Without that dialogue, the methodology has no input.

If the skill is missing, install it:

```bash
git clone -b an-orm-skill https://github.com/RelationalAI/rai-agent-skills ~/rai-skills
ln -s ~/rai-skills/skills/rai-orm-from-text ~/.claude/skills/rai-orm-from-text
```

---

## Scope boundary

- This project covers **greenfield conceptual modeling** from a domain description. If you have an existing relational schema, use the schema flow (`bootstrap.sh --schema`) which invokes the SRP — it's faster and more deterministic for that input.
- This project produces a conceptual model + PyRel translation. It does **not** include database deployment, query optimization, or runtime testing against data — those are downstream.
- The quality of the output is bounded by the quality of the dialogue. Sparse or contradictory expert input produces sparse or contradictory models.

---

## Stakeholders

| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| Modeler (you) | Authors `/gsd:*` commands, drives the dialogue, transcribes expert answers into PLAN.md / CONTEXT.md. |
| Domain expert | Provides elementary facts, confirms uniqueness, labels subtypes, accepts/rejects LLM-tier proposals. **Required at every Discuss step.** |
| Downstream consumer | Reads the final `model.py` and integrates into their RAI workload. |
